                          batch file help exist checks clear status messages 8.3 dos-compatible names model files                                                                         Batch file help                                                 In a batch file, use IF EXIST checks, clear status messages, and 8.3 DOS-compatible names for model files.                                                                                      dos boot order config.sys loads device drivers first autoexec.bat runs commands sets paths                                                                      DOS boot order                                                  CONFIG.SYS loads device drivers first, then AUTOEXEC.BAT runs commands and sets paths.                                                                                                          dosbox bundle quick local runs hardware transfer real machines                                                                                                  DOSBox use                                                      Use the DOSBox bundle for quick local runs, then use hardware transfer for real machines.                                                                                                       batch safety check exist before running large files print clear status lines step                                                                               Batch safety                                                    Check IF EXIST before running large files and print clear status lines for each step.                                                                                                           autoexec bat autoexec.bat tuning config.sys loads drivers before sets path variables required tsr tools                                                         AUTOEXEC.BAT tuning                                             CONFIG.SYS loads drivers before AUTOEXEC.BAT; then AUTOEXEC sets PATH, variables, and 